stylometry: Price sensitivity.  The demand for products varies on that fact that consumers demand certain products more than others.  This means consumers are price sensitive.  Some products will cost more than others.  For example research (data mining) at Giant Eagle found on thursdays that males who buy diapers also buys beers.  So Giant Eagle place the diapers right next to the beer and raised the prices for both only on thursdays because they knew there was a high demand for those two products on thursdays.  Management decision is the decision between possible outcomes.  No outcome is the correct answer because however, a decision may look prettier but its impossible to predict what outcome will happen.
